Initialize two pointers: left = 0 right = numbers.length - 1 
While left < right: Compute sum = numbers[left] + numbers[right]
If sum == target → return {left + 1, right + 1} (since array is 1-indexed)
If sum < target → increase left (we need a larger number)
If sum > target → decrease right (we need a smaller number)
class Solution {
    public int[] twoSum(int[] numbers, int target) {
        int left = 0;
        int right = numbers.length - 1;        
        while (left < right) {
            int sum = numbers[left] + numbers[right];
            if (sum == target) {
                return new int[]{left + 1, right + 1};
            } else if (sum < target) {
                left++;
            } else {
                right--;
            }
        }
        return new int[]{-1, -1};}}
